properties.areaDesc: Munising to Grand Marais MI; Grand Marais to Whitefish Point MI; Lake Superior East of a line from Manitou Island to Marquette MI and West of a line from Grand Marais MI to the US/Canadian Border Beyond 5NM from shore; Marquette to Munising MI; Lake Superior from Grand Marais MI to Whitefish Point MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 15 at 9:55AM EST until February 16 at 4:00AM EST by NWS Marquette MI
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and waves
6 to 11 feet expected.

* WHERE...Marquette to Munising MI, Munising to Grand Marais MI,
Grand Marais to Whitefish Point MI, Lake Superior East of a
line from Manitou Island to Marquette MI and West of a line
from Grand Marais MI to the US/Canadian Border Beyond 5NM from
shore and Lake Superior from Grand Marais MI to Whitefish
Point MI 5NM off shore to the US/Canadian border.

* WHEN...From 8 PM this evening to 4 AM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 AM EST SUNDAY
